{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775872361688,"sessionID":"ses_285c4fa67ffesWw4I4k4euQGJ4","part":{"id":"prt_d7a3b12cc001dBXcj8tuUJWpax","messageID":"msg_d7a3b0681001tZAbaUI5vKDGOF","sessionID":"ses_285c4fa67ffesWw4I4k4euQGJ4","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_5512ad17b9bc4223a9a2199b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project at /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z thoroughly. I need to understand:\n\n1. The overall project structure (top-level directories and key files)\n2. Any existing proposal.md files or similar architecture decision records\n3. The manifests module/directory structure and contents\n4. Any existing RBAC configurations (ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding)\n5. Any existing specs or requirements documents\n6. The project's naming conventions and documentation style\n\nSearch broadly - look for:\n- **/*.md files (especially proposal*, spec*, architecture*, design*)\n- **/manifests/** directories and files\n- **/*.yaml or **/*.yml files related to RBAC (rbac, role, binding, serviceaccount)\n- Any AGENTS.md, README.md, or CONTRIBUTING.md files\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of findings including file paths and key content patterns.","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_285c4da0cffebSU21QTrZh36OG (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a comprehensive understanding of the project. Here is the full summary:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Project Summary: AgentCube\n\n### 1. Overall Project Structure\n\n**Root directory:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z`\n\n**Top-level directories and key files:**\n\n| Path | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `cmd/` | Go binaries: `agentd/`, `cli/`, `picod/`, `router/`, `workloadmanager/` |\n| `pkg/` | Go packages: `agentd/`, `apis/`, `common/`, `picod/`, `router/`, `store/`, `workloadmanager/` |\n| `manifests/` | Helm chart (`charts/base/`) with templates, CRDs, and values |\n| `changes/` | 31 change requests (AR-001 through AR-031), each with proposal/design/delta-spec/tasks |\n| `client-go/` | Generated Kubernetes client-go code |\n| `python-sdk/` | (referenced in docs as `sdk-python/`) Python SDK package |\n| `ci-cd/` | CI/CD design and spec |\n| `deployment/` | Deployment design and spec |\n| `integrations/` | Dify plugin and PCAP analyzer integration spec and design |\n| `session-store/` | Redis/Valkey session store spec and design |\n| `session-routing/` | Router session routing spec and design |\n| `code-execution/` | PicoD code execution engine spec and design |\n| `cli-toolkit/` | CLI toolkit spec and design |\n| `idle-cleanup/` | Agentd idle cleanup design |\n| `testing/` | TDD manifest |\n| `test/` | E2E test scripts |\n| `go.mod` / `go.sum` | Go module: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`, Go 1.25.0 |\n| `proposal.md` | Root-level proposal (currently AR-028 content) |\n| `design.md` | Root-level design (currently AR-029 content) |\n| `delta-spec.md` | Root-level delta spec (currently AR-029 content) |\n| `tasks.md` | Root-level tasks (currently AR-023 content) |\n| `project.md` | Project context document |\n| `test_spec.md` | Test case specification (TDD) |\n| `.sdd_prompt.md` | SDD prompt template for generating design docs |\n\n**No README.md, AGENTS.md, or CONTRIBUTING.md files exist in the repository.**\n\n---\n\n### 2. Proposal/ADR Pattern\n\nThe project uses a structured **Change Request (AR)** system located in `changes/AR-NNN/`. Each AR contains exactly four files:\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `proposal.md` | Purpose, scope (in/out), impact analysis, alternatives considered, acceptance criteria, status checkboxes |\n| `design.md` | Architecture, data structures, API contracts, error handling, testing strategy, implementation steps |\n| `delta-spec.md` | Context (module, language, size, base specs), requirements in GIVEN/WHEN/THEN format, file change table |\n| `tasks.md` | Checkbox task list with dependency graph and parallelizable groups |\n\n**Root-level docs** (`proposal.md`, `design.md`, `delta-spec.md`, `tasks.md`) appear to be symlinks or copies of the current active AR. Currently they contain AR-028/AR-029/AR-023 content respectively.\n\n**AR-031** is the RBAC configuration AR and is currently a **skeleton** -- all sections contain `<!-- TODO: ... -->` placeholders.\n\n**Documentation language:** Mixed Chinese and English. Proposals tend to use Chinese for narrative sections; specs use English with RFC 2119 normative language (SHALL/SHOULD/MAY).\n\n---\n\n### 3. Manifests Module Structure\n\n```\nmanifests/\n  charts/\n    base/\n      Chart.yaml          # name: agentcube, version: 0.1.0, appVersion: 1.0.0\n      values.yaml         # Component configuration (router, workloadmanager, volcano, redis)\n      crds/\n        runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml\n        runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml\n      templates/\n        _helpers.tpl                      # Standard Helm helpers (name, fullname, labels)\n        agentcube-router.yaml             # Deployment + Service for Router\n        workloadmanager.yaml              # Deployment + Service for Workload Manager\n        rbac-router.yaml                  # Conditional RBAC for Router (SA/Role/RoleBinding)\n        rbac/\n          workloadmanager.yaml            # Unconditional RBAC for Workload Manager (SA/ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding)\n        volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml  # Optional Volcano scheduler\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Existing RBAC Configurations\n\nThere are **three distinct RBAC sets**:\n\n#### 4a. WorkloadManager (always created)\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n\n| Resource | Name | Scope |\n|----------|------|-------|\n| `ServiceAccount` | `workloadmanager` | Release namespace |\n| `ClusterRole` | `workloadmanager` | Cluster |\n| `ClusterRoleBinding` | `workloadmanager` | Cluster |\n\n**ClusterRole rules cover:**\n- `agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxes` -- full CRUD\n- `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxclaims` -- full CRUD\n- `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxtemplates` -- full CRUD\n- `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxwarmpools` -- full CRUD (+ status)\n- `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters` -- full CRUD (+ status, finalizers)\n- `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/agentruntimes` -- get/list/watch (+ status update/patch)\n- Core: `pods` (get/list/watch), `secrets` (full CRUD)\n- `authentication.k8s.io/tokenreviews` (create)\n\n#### 4b. Router (optional, gated by `router.rbac.create`)\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n\n| Resource | Name | Scope |\n|----------|------|-------|\n| `ServiceAccount` | `agentcube-router` (or custom via `router.serviceAccountName`) | Release namespace |\n| `Role` | Same as SA name | Release namespace |\n| `RoleBinding` | Same | Release namespace |\n\n**Role rules:** Core API group (`\"\"`), resource `secrets`, verbs: `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete`\n\n**Default:** `router.rbac.create: false` (disabled by default in values.yaml)\n\n#### 4c. Volcano Agent Scheduler (optional, gated by `volcano.scheduler.enabled`)\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`\n\n| Resource | Name | Scope |\n|----------|------|-------|\n| `ServiceAccount` | `volcano-agent-scheduler` | Release namespace |\n| `ClusterRole` | `volcano-agent-scheduler` | Cluster |\n| `ClusterRoleBinding` | `volcano-agent-scheduler-role` | Cluster |\n\n**ClusterRole rules:** Very extensive -- covers CRDs, pods, PVCs, PVs, nodes, namespaces, services, storage classes, pod disruption budgets, priority classes, Volcano podgroups, configmaps, leases, resource claims, device classes, node shards, etc.\n\n**Default:** `volcano.scheduler.enabled: false` (disabled by default)\n\n---\n\n### 5. Specs and Requirements Documents\n\n**Module-level spec/design pairs** (each subdirectory has both):\n\n| Directory | spec.md | design.md |\n|-----------|---------|-----------|\n| `deployment/` | Yes (96 lines, 11 requirements) | Yes (271 lines, exhaustive chart/Makefile/Dockerfile reference) |\n| `python-sdk/` | Yes (133 lines, SDK requirements) | -- |\n| `session-store/` | Yes (118 lines, store interface/Redis/Valkey) | -- |\n| `session-routing/` | Yes (115 lines, routing/proxy/JWT) | -- |\n| `code-execution/` | Yes | Yes |\n| `cli-toolkit/` | Yes | Yes |\n| `integrations/` | Yes (191 lines, Dify plugin + PCAP analyzer) | Yes |\n| `ci-cd/` | Yes | Yes |\n| `idle-cleanup/` | -- | Yes |\n\n**Additional spec documents:**\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/test_spec.md` -- TDD test case specification (29 lines, 5 categories)\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md` -- TDD manifest with test/code ratio requirements (>0.4)\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/project.md` -- Project context (45 lines)\n\n**Spec format:** Uses RFC 2119 normative language (SHALL/SHOULD/MAY) with GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenario format.\n\n---\n\n### 6. Naming Conventions and Documentation Style\n\n**Kubernetes resource naming:**\n- Lowercase kebab-case for resource names: `workloadmanager`, `agentcube-router`, `volcano-agent-scheduler`\n- Labels use `app: <name>` pattern\n- API group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` (CRDs), `agents.x-k8s.io` (sandbox), `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` (sandbox extensions)\n- CRD versions: `v1alpha1`\n\n**Go conventions:**\n- Module: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n- Packages under `pkg/`, binaries under `cmd/`\n- JSON tags use camelCase; Go structs use PascalCase\n- Apache/Volcano boilerplate on all `.go` and `.py` files\n\n**Python conventions:**\n- Package name: `agentcube` (SDK), `agentcube-sdk` (PyPI)\n- Requires Python >= 3.10\n- Uses `requests`, `PyJWT`, `cryptography`\n\n**Helm conventions:**\n- Chart API: `v1`\n- Values use dot-notation: `router.replicas`, `workloadmanager.image.repository`\n- Templates use standard Helm templating with `{{ .Values.* }}` and `{{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n- RBAC for Router is conditionally rendered with `{{- if .Values.router.rbac.create }}`\n\n**AR (Change Request) conventions:**\n- ID format: `AR-NNN` (zero-padded to 3 digits)\n- Title format: `# AR-NNN -- Short Description`\n- Metadata fields: Module, Language, Size (S/M/L)\n- Sections: Purpose, Scope (In/Out), Architecture Summary, Impact Analysis, Alternatives Considered, Acceptance Criteria, Status\n- Specs use GIVEN/WHEN/THEN format\n- Tasks use `- [ ]` checkbox format with dependency graphs\n\n**Documentation language:** Bilingual. Proposal narratives often in Chinese; specs and design docs in English. The root `project.md` is entirely in English.\n\n**No README.md, AGENTS.md, or CONTRIBUTING.md** files exist anywhere in the repository.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_285c4da0cffebSU21QTrZh36OG","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775872189937,"end":1775872361686}}}}
